Q: Mr. Maximilian is a dairy animal farmer and has 140 cows on his farm. Forty percent of the cows on his farm have a red spot, 25 percent of the cows without a red spot have a blue spot and the remaining cows do not have any spot. How many cows on the farm have no spot?
A: If Mr. Maximilian has 140 cows and 40% of them have red spots, then 40/100*140 = 56 cows have red spots. The number of cows with no red spot is 140-56 = 84 cows. Out of the 84 cows without a red spot, 25% of them have a blue spot, a total of 25/100*84 = 21 cows. The number of cows without any spot is 84-21 =63 animals. 
The answer is 63.</s>


Q: Two cars are driving on a highway.  The first car is traveling at an average speed of 60 miles per hour when the second car passes it at an average speed of 70 miles per hour.  If both cars continue on the highway at the same speed, how many miles will separate them after 2 hours?
A: In two hours, the first car will have traveled 60*2 = 120 miles. Similarly, the second car will have traveled 70*2 = 140 miles. Thus, the cars are separated by 140 - 120 = 20 miles after two hours. 
The answer is 20.</s>
